description:
Kitchen Basics - an American Original Inspired by Homemade: Everyone knows the deep, concentrated flavor of a perfect homemade stock. It's rich. It's savory. And Kitchen Basics rivals that authentic, premium taste. We craft our mouthwatering liquid gold by simmering the finest quality McCormick Gourmet herbs and spices with beef and vegetables to extract layers of hearty flavor. The result - a dark, high-quality stock that inspires quick, flavorful dinners and company-worthy feasts alike. The Heart-Healthy Choice for Ingredient-Conscious Cooks: Our stock is a key ingredient for your best culinary creations - soups, sauces, pastas, marinades, vegetables. Kitchen Basics Stock is also certified heart-healthy by the American Heart Association. Plus, with 65% less sodium than our original stock, it's still a more flavorful substitute for broth that allows you to control the flavor of your finished dishes.

Directions:
Shake before use. Kitchen Basics is an all natural product and may have naturally occurring protein deposits. These are normal and can be dissipated by heating. Do not microwave this carton. Refrigerate unused portion. Good for 7 days. Ready to use. Do not dilute. Refrigerate after opening and use within 7 days. Freeze leftover stock in freezable container or ice cube trays. Store frozen stock cubes in a resealable plastic bag and use within 60 days. Recommended use by date on package.

description:
Kosher for Passover and all year round. L'chaim to life! Matzo Balls are a delicious treat that taste great in chicken soup or as a side dish. Enjoy all of our matzo ball and matzo ball soup products throughout the year.

Directions
You Will Need: a small bowl, 2 eggs, 2 tbsp vegetable oil; To Cook: 10 cups (2-1/2 quarts) cold water; 4 quart pot.
1. Mix in a bowl 2 eggs and 2 tablespoons vegetable oil. Add contents of one packet and stir with a fork until evenly mixed. Chill in refrigerator for about 15 minutes.
2. In the meantime, pour 10 cups (2-1/2 quarts) water into pot and bring to a brisk boil. Add salt if desired. Remove chilled matzo ball mixture from refrigerator. Wet hands and form batter into matzo balls, approximately 1 inch in diameter.
3. Drop matzo balls into boiling water. Cover tightly. Reduce heat and simmer until thoroughly cooked, about 20 minutes. Each packet makes: 9-12 matzo balls.

description:
Chicken flavor with other natural flavor. Kosher-meat under the supervision of the Chief Rabbinate Haifa. Product of Israel.

Directions
Stovetop:
1. In 2-quart saucepan, bring 4 cups (32 fl oz) water to a boil; stir in contents of one pouch of soup mix.
2. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until noodles are tender. Refrigerate any unused cooked portion.

Microwave
1. In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine 4 cups (32 fl oz) water and contents of one pouch of soup mix.
2. Microwave uncovered at high (full power) 12 to 14 minutes (Microwave ovens vary; adjust times as needed) or until noodles are tender, stirring once halfway through cooking.
